body:
Added the hostname assignment back into the AbstractServer.  I don't love that the appName is a string assigned and hardcoded in each server class but it works for now.  It probably would be good to create an ApplicatioName enum for these (another ticket).
```java
 protected AbstractServer(String appName, ConfigOpts opts, String[] args) {
    this.log = LoggerFactory.getLogger(getClass().getName());
    this.applicationName = appName;
    opts.parseArgs(appName, args);
    var siteConfig = opts.getSiteConfiguration();
    this.hostname = siteConfig.get(appName+ Property.SERVER_ADDRESS_BIND_SUFFIX); <====
    context = new ServerContext(siteConfig);
    SecurityUtil.serverLogin(siteConfig);
    log.info("Version " + Constants.VERSION);
    log.info("Instance " + context.getInstanceID());
    ServerUtil.init(context, appName);
    this.metricsSystem = Metrics.initSystem(getClass().getSimpleName());
    TraceUtil.enableServerTraces(hostname, appName, context.getConfiguration());
    if (context.getSaslParams() != null) {
      // Server-side "client" check to make sure we're logged in as a user we expect to be
      context.enforceKerberosLogin();
    }
  }
```

Also added a deprecation property override so it may make it easier to deprecate the --address option .  Still reviewing.

```
 /**
   * Performs special processing of deprecated options.
   * Could be cleaned up periodically as deprecations are deleted
   * @param option
   * @param value
   */
  private static void processDeprecation(String option, String value){
    if ("-s".equals(option)){
      deprecated_overrides.add(Property.GC_SAFEMODE.getKey()+"=true");
    }
  }
```
So now I can get rid of 
`safemode = opts.safeMode || getConfiguration().getBoolean(Property.GC_SAFEMODE);`
and replace with just
`safemode = getConfiguration().getBoolean(Property.GC_SAFEMODE);`
